---
// Layouts
import Layout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<Layout title="M. Shrief :: Blog" description="Blogs about Web development in the Backend and Frontend.">
  <main>
    <section >
      <h2>Frontend</h2>
      <div class="single">
        <h3><a href="/blog/mpa-vs-spa">MPAs VS SPAs</a></h3>
        <p>We'll discuss Multi-Page Application (MPA) VS Single-Page Application (SPA) in terms of Rendering, State Management and Routing.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="single">
        <h3><a href="/blog/intro-to-astro">Introduction to Astro</a></h3>
        <p>Breaking Astro main conceptes and advantages, and it's imapct on developers and the market, in my view.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="series">
        <h3>Migrate your Vuejs SPA to SSR with Astro (Series)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li class="series-item"><a href="/blog/migrate-vuejs-spa-to-ssr-with-astro/intro/">Intro</a><br>
            We'll take another route for migrating your Vuejs SPA with Astro instead of Nuxt, we'll disucss the difference between both, and why you should choose Astro instead.</li>
          <li class="series-item"><a href="/blog/migrate-vuejs-spa-to-ssr-with-astro/setup/">Setup</a><br>
            Setting up our project's boilerplate and configuration</li>
          <li class="series-item"><a href="/blog/migrate-vuejs-spa-to-ssr-with-astro/strategy/">Strategy</a><br>
            Recommending a form of steps to accomplish a complete migration form Vuejs SPA to SSR with Astro.</li>
          <!-- <li class="series-item"><a href="/blog/migrate-vuejs-spa-to-ssr-with-astro/rendering/">Rendering</a></li> -->
          <!-- <li class="series-item"><a href="/blog/migrate-vuejs-spa-to-ssr-with-astro/routing/">Routing</a></li> -->
          <li class="series-item"><a href="/blog/migrate-vuejs-spa-to-ssr-with-astro/state-management/">State Management</a><br>
            We'll discuss how to manage your state in as SSR that uses Astro and Vuejs, either by using Pinia or just using Composition API.</li>
          <!-- <li class="series-item"><a href="/blog/migrate-vuejs-spa-to-ssr-with-astro/dark-light-themes/">Adding Dark/Light Theme</a><br>
            We'll discus how to add Dark/Light Themes to Astro projects, using a native approach.</li> -->
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
    <!-- 
        <h2>Backend</h2>
        <h2>DevOps</h2>
      -->

    <div class="all-blogs" >
      <a href="/blog/all">All Blogs</a>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
  @import "../../assets/mixins.scss";
  main {
    width: 80%;
    margin: 1rem auto;
    @include mQ($breakpoint-sm) {
      width: 95%;
      h1 {
        font-size: 1.4rem;
      }
    }
    h2 {
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
  .series {
    list-style: none;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 550;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-radius: 1rem 0;
    background-color: var(--surface1);
    @include mQ($breakpoint-sm) {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
    }
    .series-item {
      position: relative;
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      margin: 0.5rem auto;
      border-radius: 1rem;
      // list-style: none;
      @include mQ($breakpoint-sm) {
        padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
        margin: 0.5rem auto;
      }
      a {
        @include blog-link;
      }
    }
  }
  .single {
    list-style: none;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 550;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-radius: 1rem 0;
    background-color: var(--surface1);
    @include mQ($breakpoint-sm) {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
    }
    a {
      @include blog-link;
    }
    p {
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }
  }
  .all-blogs {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0 1rem ;
    background-color: var(--brand);
    a {
      color: #fff;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }
    @include mQ($breakpoint-sm) {
      padding: 0.5rem;
      a {
        font-size:0.8rem;
      }
    }
  }
</style>

